{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6009d603-63c4-4f27-8802-635629199c65","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```jsonc\n// Change\n\"version\": \"10.0.100\"\n// To\n\"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Change\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 AS build\n# To\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking API changes relevant to your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5de34c05-76f0-46cb-bff8-93d99bfe55f9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading — I can answer directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nHere's what they need to change:\n\n1. **csproj** — `TargetFramework`: `net10.0` → `net11.0`\n2. **global.json** — SDK version: `10.0.100` → `11.0.100`\n3. **Dockerfile** — base images: `aspnet:10.0` → `aspnet:11.0`, `sdk:10.0` → `sdk:11.0`\n\n\nI'll provide a clear, concise answer with the key files they need to update.","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"884A:1EBB0A:1DFF913:217458C:69FA9D62"},"id":"2b8731ce-a295-4a92-9c8f-53a362dd0d1a","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:46:18.299Z","parentId":"faf58908-7cf1-4d08-9162-0d852b4e054e"}
